.TH "fm10k_update_mc_addr_pf" 9 "fm10k_update_mc_addr_pf" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
fm10k_update_mc_addr_pf \- Update device multicast addresses
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "s32" fm10k_update_mc_addr_pf
.BI "(struct fm10k_hw *hw "  ","
.BI "u16 glort "  ","
.BI "const u8 *mac "  ","
.BI "u16 vid "  ","
.BI "bool add "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "hw" 12
pointer to the HW structure
.IP "glort" 12
base resource tag for this request
.IP "mac" 12
MAC address to add/remove from table
.IP "vid" 12
VLAN ID to add/remove from table
.IP "add" 12
Indicates if this is an add or remove operation

This function is used to add or remove multicast MAC addresses for
the PF.
